OL,3,CElectric HGVs being trialled across
OL,4,Cthe UK in a bid to help lorries go
OL,5,Cgreen
OL,7,FCurrently road-freight makes up 5
OL,8,Fpercent of the UK's emissions, so
OL,9,Fthere is an urgent need to de-
OL,10,Fcarbonise the industry. Now, a group
OL,11,Fof major UK companies - including
OL,12,FNestle and John Lewis - have begun
OL,13,Ftrialling a fleet of electric lorries
OL,14,Fto find out exactly what they're
OL,15,Fcapable of, as ITV News Science
OL,16,FCorrespondent Martin Stew reports.
OL,18,FElectric heavy goods vehicles (HGVs)
OL,19,Fare being trialled across the UK, in a
OL,20,Fbid to help freight operators reduce
OL,21,Fcarbon emissions.
